user_message: Show the leiden UMAP for T cell.
bot_response: The Leiden UMAP for T cells is ready and available as an interactive plot in the UI. You can view the clustering of T cells based on the Leiden algorithm, which helps in identifying distinct subpopulations within the T cell dataset. Please check the UI for the detailed visualization.

The overall UMAP visualization is ready and available for you to view in the UI. It includes the cell types currently available in your dataset: B cells, Epithelial cells, Glial cells, Mast cells, Mononuclear phagocytes, Natural killer cells, Stromal cells, and T cells. You can explore the interactive plot to see how these cell types are distributed across the UMAP space.
